  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Each configuration file has a duplicate `CONFIG_NAME` that can only result in conflicting values, and it makes it more difficult to consolidate the config files.\r\n\r\nDiscussion (@michaelsproul, @mcdee, @rolfyone): https://discord.com/channels/595666850260713488/710831784991916072/823906028600033351\r\n\r\n> there's this weird exception right now, the `CONFIG_NAME` variable is duplicated between all configs (and might be different for unknown reasons)\r\n\r\n> Why does CONFIG_NAME need to be in altair.yml?\r\n\r\n> Legacy choice, I think it can be removed. My intention was always to have unique variables, simple key-value, yaml compatible, and ability to consolidate into a single namespace easily (for compatibility with env vars)\r\n\r\n----\r\n\r\nI think it's valuable to not have duplicate variables, and avoid dependency on them before we introduce a stable version of the first fork (Altair). In the future we may consolidate the files into a single YAML, and client implementers may do this in their internal config representation already.\r\n",
