    "body": "Right, so the `spec.CONFIG_NAME` is for making `with_configs` work. I think it's good to keep the current separate per-fork-per-config files so that we can compare them with the specs easily.\r\n\r\nA simple solution here, similar to ToC generation:\r\n1. Add makefile command `make merge_config` to create merged config files: `configs/merged/<SPEC_CODE_NAME>_<CONFIG_NAME>.yaml`.\r\n    - `phase0_mainnet.yaml`, `altair_mainnet.yaml`, `phase0_minimal.yaml`, `altair_minimal.yaml`.\r\n    - Each merged config contains the previous forks' config + current fork config.\r\n    - The merged file doesn't contain `CONFIG_NAME` field, but it checks if there are any conflicts (except for ` CONFIG_NAME`) between the atomic config files when calling the makefile command.\r\n2. Add a CI job to check if the merged config files are correct.\r\n3. Output these merged config files to test vector suite output files.\r\n",
